# 2D Spectroscopy Simulations and Experimental Data

This repository contains code and supporting files used for the manuscript:

**Multidimensional semiclassical single- and double-quantum spectroscopy of anharmonic molecular polaritons**

**Authors:** Michael Reitz, Harsh Bhakta, Wei Xiong, and Joel Yuen-Zhou.

The repository contains experimental 2D infrared spectroscopy data and simulation code for computing single-quantum and double-quantum coherence spectra. The code is organized into separate workflows for single-quantum (`1Q`) and double-quantum coherence (`DQC`) calculations.

The general workflow is:

1. Solve the equations of motion up to third order.
2. Fourier transform the resulting time-domain response functions.
3. Plot the simulated spectra.
4. For 1Q: Compare the simulated spectra with the experimental data in the `data/` folder.

## Repository structure

```text
.
├── data/
│   ├── *.csv
│   │   └── Long waiting-time experimental spectra measured at different excitation intensities
│   └── specdat_yxavg_fwhm_03#02.mat
│       └── Early-time complex 2DIR dynamics from -0.3 to 9.9 ps
│
├── 1Q/
│   ├── <equations-of-motion script>
│   └── <Fourier-transform and plotting script>
│
└── DQC/
    ├── <equations-of-motion script>
    └── <Fourier-transform and plotting script>
